<%#
  CZID-285 — Layer 3 identity-verification + export-screening start page.

  ⚠️ TODO(counsel): ALL user-facing copy here is a PLACEHOLDER with legal weight and MUST be drafted or
  approved by counsel before go-live (design doc §10). Do not treat the text below as final.

  Minimal, dependency-free skeleton (no React/webpack entry) so the gate is functional now. The real IDV
  vendor hand-off (embedding the vendor's verification flow / redirect) is wired when the vendor is chosen
  — TODO(vendor).
%>
<div class="export-control-clearance" style="max-width: 720px; margin: 64px auto; padding: 0 24px; font-family: 'Open Sans', sans-serif;">
  <h1 style="font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px;">
    <%# TODO(counsel): heading copy %>
    Identity verification required
  </h1>

  <div style="background:#f6f8fa; border:1px solid #d0d7de; border-radius:6px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:24px; line-height:1.6;">
    <p><strong>PLACEHOLDER — pending counsel-approved text (TODO(counsel)).</strong></p>
    <p>
      Access to export-controlled data and functions on this service requires a verified identity that has
      been screened against U.S. denied- and restricted-party lists. To proceed, you will complete identity
      verification with our verification provider; your identity will then be screened before access is granted.
    </p>
    <p>
      [The exact language, the verification method, the applicable screening lists, and the handling of a
      screening result are counsel-owned and will replace this placeholder before enforcement is enabled.]
    </p>
  </div>

  <%= form_with url: export_control_clearances_path, method: :post, local: true do %>
    <p style="color:#57606a; font-size:13px; margin-bottom:20px;">
      Clearance version: <%= @clearance_version %> &nbsp;·&nbsp; Provider: <%= @idv_provider %>
    </p>

    <%#
      TODO(vendor): replace this button with the chosen IDV vendor's hand-off (e.g. an embedded
      verification widget or a redirect to the vendor's hosted flow). This synchronous submit exists so the
      fail-closed gate is exercisable now — with the reference stub it records a PENDING clearance and the
      gate keeps the user out (deny), which is the correct dark-mode behavior.
    %>
    <button type="submit"
            style="background:#0969da; color:#fff; border:none; border-radius:6px; padding:10px 20px; font-size:15px; cursor:pointer;">
      <%# TODO(counsel): button label %>
      Begin identity verification
    </button>
  <% end %>
</div>
